main event: Observers saw a silver colored object over Woodbridge - Manassas, Virginia for over three hours on 1/10/62.
interesting points: The object was seen at different locations, indicating potential multiple observations., It was first observed by civilians and later by an airman., The object emitted a red light that blinked three times, pausing before repeating., The sightings occurred at dusk with visual measurements reported., Investigators concluded the sightings may be attributed to a satellite or an aircraft.
witness description: Civilians and airmen reported the sightings and gave identical descriptions of the object.
